.SH git-amend
.SS DESCRIPTION
.PP
Add actual modified and added files to the last commit.
.PP
git commit
amend (https://git-scm.com/book/id/v2/Git-Tools-Rewriting-History#_git_amend)
that always work (even if it was pushed to the remote)
.SS How?
.IP \[bu] 2
Soft reset of the last commit.
ie:
.RS 2
.IP \[bu] 2
Delete the commit (locally and remotely)
.IP \[bu] 2
Put the files of the deleted commit in the index
.RE
.IP \[bu] 2
Recreate a commit with all files
.IP \[bu] 2
If the last commit was tagged
.RS 2
.IP \[bu] 2
Delete the tag
.IP \[bu] 2
Delete the GitHub release
.RE
.SS SYNOPSIS
.IP
.nf
\f[C]
Add files to the last commit
git-amend  [Commit Message]
\f[R]
.fi
.PP
If the commit message is not given, it will take the message of the last
commit.
.SS See also
.IP \[bu] 2
git commit amend official
documentation (https://git-scm.com/book/id/v2/Git-Tools-Rewriting-History#_git_amend)
.IP \[bu] 2
git absorb plugin command (https://github.com/tummychow/git-absorb/)
that tries do the same job
